In England, in the seven days to 02 October, there were 188,105 new confirmed cases (332.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 September, there were 189,203 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 1% (1,098 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 07 October is 6,845,186 (12,104.6 cases per 100,000 population).
